description:
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will assist the Nursing team in the delivery of a rehabilitation service to In Patients in Bronglais General Hospital, Aberystwyth on a full time, permanent basis. This will involve a range of therapy interventions and treatments to help patients reach their optimum level of independence for discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder should have previous experience working within a health or social care setting . You will be expected to work alongside both the therapy and nursing teams on our Acute Stroke ward to help promote a productive rehab pathway from assessment to discharge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to work well as part of a multidisciplinary team, be self motivated, be able to prioritise delegated tasks and show a willingness to undertake self-development. You must be well organised, be a good communicator and be willing to work flexibly in new and changing environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 25/11/2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBeth JamesJob titleSenior SisterEmail addressbeth.j.james@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01970 613994&lt;/p&gt;
